<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Song_sparrow&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite class="citation journal">Beecher, M.D.; Campbell, S.E.; Stoddard, P.K. (1994). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/91/4/1450.pdf">"Correlation of Song Learning and Territory Establishment Strategies in the Song Sparrow"</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/PNAS" class="mw-redirect" title="PNAS">Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA</a></i>. <b>91</b> (4): 1450–1454.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASong+sparrow&amp;rft.atitle=Correlation+of+Song+Learning+and+Territory+Establishment+Strategies+in+the+Song+Sparrow&amp;rft.au=Campbell%2C+S.E.&amp;rft.aufirst=M.D.&amp;rft.aulast=Beecher&amp;rft.au=Stoddard%2C+P.K.&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fcgi%2Freprint%2F91%2F4%2F1450.pdf&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.jtitle=Proc.+Natl.+Acad.+Sci.+USA&amp;rft.pages=1450-1454&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=91" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite class="citation journal">Stoddard, Beecher; Horning, C.L.; Campbell, S.E. (1991). "Recognition of individual neighbors by song in the song sparrow, a species with song repertoires". <i>Behavioral Ecology and Sociobiology</i>. <b>29</b> (3): 211–215.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASong+sparrow&amp;rft.atitle=Recognition+of+individual+neighbors+by+song+in+the+song+sparrow%2C+a+species+with+song+repertoires&amp;rft.au=Campbell%2C+S.E.&amp;rft.aufirst=Beecher&amp;rft.au=Horning%2C+C.L.&amp;rft.aulast=Stoddard&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.jtitle=Behavioral+Ecology+and+Sociobiology&amp;rft.pages=211-215&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=29" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite class="citation journal">O'Loghlen, A.L.; Beecher (1997). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://faculty.washington.edu/beecher/O&amp;B1-ab97.pdf">"Sexual preferences for mate song types in female song sparrows"</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(PDF)</span>. <i>Animal Behaviour</i>. <b>53</b> (4): 835–841.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASong+sparrow&amp;rft.atitle=Sexual+preferences+for+mate+song+types+in+female+song+sparrows&amp;rft.au=Beecher&amp;rft.aufirst=A.L.&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Loghlen&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ffaculty.washington.edu%2Fbeecher%2FO%26B1-ab97.pdf&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.jtitle=Animal+Behaviour&amp;rft.pages=835-841&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=53" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite class="citation journal">Smith, J.N.M.; et al. (1997). "A metapopulation approach to the population biology of the Song Sparrow Melospiza melodia". <i>Ibis</i>. <b>138</b> (4): 120–128.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASong+sparrow&amp;rft.atitle=A+metapopulation+approach+to+the+population+biology+of+the+Song+Sparrow+Melospiza+melodia&amp;rft.aufirst=J.N.M.&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.jtitle=Ibis&amp;rft.pages=120-128&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=138" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> <span class="citation-comment" style="display:none; color:#33aa33">CS1 maint: Explicit use of et al. (<a href="/wiki/Category:CS1_maint:_Explicit_use_of_et_al." title="Category:CS1 maint: Explicit use of et al.">link</a>)</span></li>
</ul>
